            <p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/grounded-2">Grounded 2</a> has just received a massive new update called The Toxic Tangle, which is adding a new Garden biome, new enemies, and a rideable ladybug with a gun mounted on it. Obviously!</p>
<p>The Toxic Tangle update is the first major update to the game <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/grounded-2-is-celebrating-its-release-with-a-chance-to-win-a-10-foot-fluffy-ant-you-can-use-to-frighten-a-child">since its Early Access release back in 2025</a>. The Garden, overgrown with vines and towering structures, is a messy new addition that players are now able to explore. It's also littered with new enemies and resources to collect, so you'll need to keep an eye out as you venture between the pumpkins.</p>
<p>Grounded 2 will also let people ride a new Ladybug Buddy, which should help you navigate through this new landscape. It's packing a mounted water cannon on its back which you can use to fend off all manner of creepy crawlies, and is itself a tough creature to take down.</p>

